Accessibility validation utilized automated tools (WAVE, axe DevTools) and manual screen reader testing (NVDA, VoiceOver) to verify semantic heading structures, form label associations, and keyboard navigation operability. Performance validation confirmed Lighthouse scores exceeding 90 for Performance, Accessibility, Best Practices, and SEO categories.

Client requirement validation verified the absence of prohibited animations, confirmation of minimal aesthetic implementation, and verification of fast loading metrics (sub-three-second initial paint times). Final sign-off procedures included stakeholder review of integrated pages, packaging design approval, and formal acceptance documentation acknowledging deliverable completion.

