Collaborative development among three independent contributors introduced version control conflicts, design inconsistency risks, and communication overhead. Challenges included conflicting CSS class naming conventions between developers, divergent interpretations of responsive behavior requirements, and overlapping responsibilities during integration phases. Remote work weeks exacerbated coordination difficulties due to asynchronous communication delays and lack of immediate peer consultation availability.

